 been heading south.\", \"from\": 777, \"to\": 919, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Those Brazil-based Games\", \"from\": 777, \"to\": 801}, {\"ngram\": \"a massive 27 million viewers\", \"from\": 811, \"to\": 839}, {\"ngram\": \"prime time\", \"from\": 843, \"to\": 853}, {\"ngram\": \"the key viewership arrow\", \"from\": 871, \"to\": 895}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Pyeongchang Winter Games in 2018 averaged 19.8 million viewers - a new low at the time that was later shattered by the Summer Olympics in Tokyo, which averaged 15.6 million viewers in prime time across NBC's various television and digital platforms in August 2021.Per Sports Media Watch,the Tokyo Games were the first Summer Olympics to average fewer American viewers than the preceding Winter Games since Athens in 2004, which followed Salt Lake City in 2002.\", \"from\": 920, \"to\": 1384, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 924, \"end\": 935, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2018_Winter_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9991398816134419, \"rank\": 0.0008608588274691602, \"text\": \"Pyeongchang\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2018_Winter_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2018_Winter_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 936, \"end\": 948, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2022_Winter_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999017332902261, \"rank\": 9.827636673212601e-05, \"text\": \"Winter Games\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2022_Winter_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2022_Winter_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1062, \"end\": 1067, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999954525, \"rank\": 4.146060973762883e-12, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1275, \"end\": 1283, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Television_in_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999999008651, \"rank\": 9.876695291407208e-11, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Television_in_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Television_in_the_United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1330, \"end\": 1336, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999998317198475, \"rank\": 1.6827989553830808e-07, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1361, \"end\": 1375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salt_Lake_City\", \"score\": 0.9991016930700838, \"rank\": 0.0008991146103805178, \"text\": \"Salt Lake City\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salt_Lake_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salt_Lake_City\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"19.8 million viewers\", \"from\": 966, \"to\": 986}, {\"ngram\": \"a new low\", \"from\": 989, \"to\": 998}, {\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 1002, \"to\": 1010}, {\"ngram\": \"the Summer Olympics\", \"from\": 1039, \"to\": 1058}, {\"ngram\": \"15.6 million viewers\", \"from\": 1084, \"to\": 1104}, {\"ngram\": \"prime time\", \"from\": 1108, \"to\": 1118}, {\"ngram\": \"NBC's various television\", \"from\": 1126, \"to\": 1150}, {\"ngram\": \"digital platforms\", \"from\": 1155, \"to\": 1172}, {\"ngram\": \"August 2021.Per Sports Media Watch\", \"from\": 1176, \"to\": 1210}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tokyo Games\", \"from\": 1211, \"to\": 1226}, {\"ngram\": \"the first Summer Olympics\", \"from\": 1232, \"to\": 1257}, {\"ngram\": \"the preceding Winter Games\", \"from\": 1297, \"to\": 1323}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then, the Beijing Winter Olympics in February 2022 were the least-watched Games in prime time on NBC ever,averaging 10.7 million viewers per night on television, with that number rising slightly to 11.4 million including all other viewing platforms.\", \"from\": 1386, \"to\": 1635, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1396, \"end\": 1419, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2022_Winter_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Beijing Winter Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2022_Winter_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2022_Winter_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"February\", \"from\": 1423, \"to\": 1431}, {\"ngram\": \"the least-watched Games\", \"from\": 1442, \"to\": 1465}, {\"ngram\": \"prime time\", \"from\": 1469, \"to\": 1479}, {\"ngram\": \"NBC\", \"from\": 1483, \"to\": 1486}, {\"ngram\": \"10.7 million viewers\", \"from\": 1502, \"to\": 1522}, {\"ngram\": \"night\", \"from\": 1527, \"to\": 1532}, {\"ngram\": \"television\", \"from\": 1536, \"to\": 1546}, {\"ngram\": \"that number\", \"from\": 1553, \"to\": 1564}, {\"ngram\": \"all other viewing platforms\", \"from\": 1607, \"to\": 1634}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Much of this, of course, was out of NBCUniversal's control.\", \"from\": 1637, \"to\": 1696, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1673, \"end\": 1685, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\", \"score\": 0.9999999999472493, \"rank\": 5.275274560285361e-11, \"text\": \"NBCUniversal\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"course\", \"from\": 1654, \"to\": 1660}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Tokyo Games were delayed a year because of the coronavirus pandemic and the run-up to those Games was joyless given the state of the world.\", \"from\": 1697, \"to\": 1840, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Tokyo Games\", \"from\": 1697, \"to\": 1712}, {\"ngram\": \"the coronavirus pandemic\", \"from\": 1744, \"to\": 1768}, {\"ngram\": \"the run-up\", \"from\": 1773, \"to\": 1783}, {\"ngram\": \"those Games\", \"from\": 1787, \"to\": 1798}, {\"ngram\": \"joyless\", \"from\": 1803, \"to\": 1810}, {\"ngram\": \"the state\", \"from\": 1817, \"to\": 1826}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1830, \"to\": 1839}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Complicating matters was the time zone - Tokyo is 13 hours ahead of the East Coast of the United States.\", \"from\": 1841, \"to\": 1945, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1882, \"end\": 1887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999954525, \"rank\": 4.146060973762883e-12, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1931, \"end\": 1944, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999996488832655, \"rank\": 3.5111532418805213e-07, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Complicating matters\", \"from\": 1841, \"to\": 1861}, {\"ngram\": \"the time zone\", \"from\": 1866, \"to\": 1879}, {\"ngram\": \"the East Coast\", \"from\": 1909, \"to\": 1923}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Beijing Games headwinds included a focus on the politics and human rights abuses in China, a global pandemic continuing to rage, a lack of household names compared to otherOlympics, and Olympic fatigue given the Tokyo Games wrapped up just six months earlier, among other reasons.\", \"from\": 1946, \"to\": 2230, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2034, \"end\": 2039, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999999998126441, \"rank\": 1.8658692698763478e-10, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Beijing Games headwinds\", \"from\": 1946, \"to\": 1973}, {\"ngram\": \"a focus\", \"from\": 1983, \"to\": 1990}, {\"ngram\": \"the politics\", \"from\": 1994, \"to\": 2006}, {\"ngram\": \"human rights abuses\", \"from\": 2011, \"to\": 2030}, {\"ngram\": \"a global pandemic\", \"from\": 2041, \"to\": 2058}, {\"ngram\": \"a lack\", \"from\": 2079, \"to\": 2085}, {\"ngram\": \"household names\", \"from\": 2089, \"to\": 2104}, {\"ngram\": \"otherOlympics\", \"from\": 2117, \"to\": 2130}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic fatigue\", \"from\": 2136, \"to\": 2151}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tokyo Games\", \"from\": 2158, \"to\": 2173}, {\"ngram\": \"other reasons\", \"from\": 2216, \"to\": 2229}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I see Paris as a chance for the Olympics to get its mojo back,\\\" said Bob Costas, who hosted NBC's prime-time Olympics coverage 11 times, a broadcasting standard that is unlikely to be topped.\", \"from\": 2232, \"to\": 2424, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2239, \"end\": 2244, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.3233039095557754e-25, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2302, \"end\": 2305, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Weinstein\", \"score\": 0.9999998638622948, \"rank\": 1.3613779099956233e-07, \"text\": \"Bob\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Weinstein\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Weinstein\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a chance\", \"from\": 2248, \"to\": 2256}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2261, \"to\": 2273}, {\"ngram\": \"its mojo\", \"from\": 2281, \"to\": 2289}, {\"ngram\": \"NBC's prime-time Olympics coverage\", \"from\": 2325, \"to\": 2359}, {\"ngram\": \"a broadcasting standard\", \"from\": 2370, \"to\": 2393}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Jim McKay hosted eight times for ABC.)\", \"from\": 2425, \"to\": 2464, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2426, \"end\": 2435, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jim_McKay\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.2395843888465955e-77, \"text\": \"Jim McKay\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jim_McKay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jim_McKay\"}, {\"begin\": 2459, \"end\": 2462, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Broadcasting_Company\", \"score\": 0.9999999995279722, \"rank\": 4.718434330734244e-10, \"text\": \"ABC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Broadcasting_Company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Broadcasting_Company\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The real problem \\u2026 came with the two COVID Olympics, one of which was postponed.\", \"from\": 2465, \"to\": 2546, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The real problem\", \"from\": 2466, \"to\": 2482}, {\"ngram\": \"the two COVID Olympics\", \"from\": 2495, \"to\": 2517}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With the absence of crowds and family and friends on hand, a lot of things that make the Olympics a great television show were missing.\", \"from\": 2547, \"to\": 2682, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the absence\", \"from\": 2552, \"to\": 2563}, {\"ngram\": \"crowds\", \"from\": 2567, \"to\": 2573}, {\"ngram\": \"family\", \"from\": 2578, \"to\": 2584}, {\"ngram\": \"friends\", \"from\": 2589, \"to\": 2596}, {\"ngram\": \"hand\", \"from\": 2600, \"to\": 2604}, {\"ngram\": \"a lot\", \"from\": 2606, \"to\": 2611}, {\"ngram\": \"things\", \"from\": 2615, \"to\": 2621}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2632, \"to\": 2644}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The absence of crowds for any sports event diminishes it greatly.\", \"from\": 2683, \"to\": 2748, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The absence\", \"from\": 2683, \"to\": 2694}, {\"ngram\": \"crowds\", \"from\": 2698, \"to\": 2704}, {\"ngram\": \"any sports event\", \"from\": 2709, \"to\": 2725}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement \\\"I think NBC coped with it as best they possibly could.\", \"from\": 2750, \"to\": 2820, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"NBC\", \"from\": 2773, \"to\": 2776}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They had cameras in a family's living room, but it's just not the same.\", \"from\": 2821, \"to\": 2892, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"cameras\", \"from\": 2830, \"to\": 2837}, {\"ngram\": \"a family's living room\", \"from\": 2841, \"to\": 2863}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So there is that.\", \"from\": 2893, \"to\": 2910, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Plus, with the China Olympics, I think by then there was a broad understanding of something that I tried to make clear in 2008 (the Summer Olympics, which Beijing also hosted) and then again in 2014 (the Winter Games in Sochi, Russia), which is that the IOC has a troubling affinity for authoritarian regimes with horrible human rights records.\", \"from\": 2911, \"to\": 3255, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2926, \"end\": 2931, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999999998126441, \"rank\": 1.8658692698763478e-10, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 3066, \"end\": 3073, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999856881655494, \"rank\": 1.4312015098082443e-05, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3131, \"end\": 3136, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2014_Winter_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.99999999708416, \"rank\": 2.